The method should return an integer value representing the total importance value of the employee and all their direct and indirect subordinates.
If the `id` does not exist in the `employees` list, the method should return The method should handle the case where the employee has no direct or indirect subordinates and return the importance value of the employee alone.
The method should handle the case where the employee has direct subordinates but no indirect subordinates and return the importance value of the employee and their direct subordinates.
The method should handle the case where the employee has indirect subordinates but no direct subordinates and return the importance value of the employee and their indirect subordinates.
The method should handle the case where the employee has both direct and indirect subordinates and return the importance value of the employee, their direct subordinates, and their indirect subordinates.
